biclusterHandling is a function that handles the bicluster output and responds to the main program by having modifying the passed parameters.

Parameters:
INPUT (leda::matrix) input matrix obtained from the given input file sources/data_sources
biclusters (leda::list<list<GENES>>)filled with the GENE names provided by the data file
matrixBiclusters (leda::list<leda::matrix>)is used H-value calculation we need this param to obtain submatrices of biclusters
H-values (leda::list) are used in order to have a corresponding value obtained with the id of biclusters
Hmax (double) Hmax is a value that stores max H-value
minBicSize to control bicluster sizes
maxBicSize to control bicluster sizes
biclustering (int) is for choosing different biclustering outputs, We have to do that since each alg. has different output from its tool.
dimension1(int) size of the data row dimension
dimension2(int) size of the data column dimension
